The paper discusses the technical challenges of detecting and analyzing online radicalization, which involves analyzing user-generated content on various online platforms. This falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CR) and cyber systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses natural language processing techniques for analyzing text data (cs.CL) and data mining techniques for analyzing large amounts of data (cs.SI, cs.SD).
